Bola Ahmed Tinubu, presidential candidate of the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC), has won the presidential election in Jigawa State. Tinubu won the 19 LGAs of the state with a total of 421,390 votes, according to the INEC resident electoral commissioner in the state, Muhammad Bashar, a professor, who declared Tinubu as winner at the state collation centre on Monday. Bashar said he defeated the candidate of the People Democratic Party, (PDP) Atiku Abubakar, who scored 386,587 votes.